org.jhove2.module.format.utf8.unicode
Class CodeBlock

java.lang.Object
  org.jhove2.module.format.utf8.unicode.CodeBlock
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<CodeBlock>
@Persistent
public class CodeBlock
extends Object
implements Comparable<CodeBlock>

A Unicode code block, a range of code points associated with a named language or script system. Code blocks are initialized from a properties file formatted the same as the Unicode database (UCB) file Blocks.txt: start..end; name with the starting and ending code point (in hexadecimal), and block name.

Author:
mstrong, slabrams
